tip.text: Excellent service and food. A nice balance of selections between poultry and seafood. Onion soup and risotto were great. Outdoor bar is nice but the drinks are questionable. Get the Camembert dip.

tip.text: Cheaper brunch venue compared to other places. Limited menu: eggs and sandwiches. Menu is mounted on the wall. Coffee is pretty good. If you like, they have a Vegemite sandwich.

location.state: Singapore

tip.text: The space is designed for people who love taking selfies - modern with plenty of natural light. Got a lobster salad and it was drenched in dressing. Dessert was good. Good place to get day drunk.

tip.text: Housed in an Art Deco building. Good cocktails, ok burger. Clueless waiter didn't know what a happy hour was. Asked for truffle fries (seen in tips on foursquare) and he said they don't have it.
Boutique resort on Kwai Noi River that offers great view and privacy with only 8 rooms. About a15-min drive to the city center. Only 5 items on the breakfast menu. Lots of bugs and WiFi isn't great.

formattedAddress: จังหวัดกาญจนบุรี 71000

tip.text: Got the crab cake benedict and it was bland. Hollandaise sauce was tasteless and crab cakes were dry. Maybe it was in a bad day. I'd go back and try something else.

location.state: กรุงเทพมหานคร
formattedAddress: กรุงเทพมหานคร 10330

tip.text: The most unpretentious cafe in a hipster area. It is important that you try their fruit tarts. They're not too sweet and taste like heaven in your mouth. True fact.
In the middle of the mall and mostly filled with tourists. Great food and service but super pricey. Grilled cod and a cup of tea cost around SGD 45. All dishes and desserts are infused with tea.

location.address: #B2-89/89A, The Shoppes at Marina Bay Sands

tip.text: Only 5-6 items on the weekend brunch menu. Food is great. Inefficient service with snooty attitude. Staff don't know how to seat diners properly and don't know which ingredients already ran out.
Definitely get the crustacean bowl. Need a better bread roll. The sun dried tomato lobster is bland. Get the spicy or garlic lobster instead. Reservation is needed.
Great deal on lunch set. Only available on weekdays. Skip the tempura and other usual stuff since they're not that great. Try the fusion dishes or things that sound complicated.
